Disable the TrackPoint in Wayland
=================================

echo $XDG_SESSION_TYPE 

grep -i trackpoint /proc/bus/input/devices

sudo nano /etc/udev/rules.d/99-disable-trackpoint.rules

SUBSYSTEM=="input", ATTRS{name}=="TPPS/2 IBM TrackPoint", ENV{ID_INPUT_POINTINGSTICK}="0", ENV{ID_INPUT}="0"

[Note: My trackpoint is TPPS/2 IBM TrackPoint. You can replace it with your one.]

If you experience mouse getting stuck or sluggish, use this instead in the 99.disable-trackpoint.rules file:

ATTRS{name}=="TPPS/2 IBM TrackPoint", ENV{LIBINPUT_IGNORE_DEVICE}="1"

sudo udevadm control --reload-rules && sudo udevadm trigger
sudo reboot



Undo / Re-enable TrackPoint (if needed)
=======================================

sudo rm /etc/udev/rules.d/99-disable-trackpoint.rules
sudo reboot

